The paper focuses on the problem of automated repair of software vulnerabilities, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed approach uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the application of the proposed approach to other problems similar to code repair, such as grammar correction or sentiment translation, which are related to natural language processing (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of software vulnerabilities, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a technique for mapping from one domain to another without requiring paired labeled examples, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL).
